text: Social anxiety has destroyed my life    I m often seen as the quit kid ever since I can remember I ve always kept to my self never feeling the need to talk to people  It wasn t until middle school I realized how different I was  I found my self extremely nervous in some environments but I was still able to complete the task at hand without letting my nerves get to me  It wasn t till  th or  th grade  I was in my music class which my crush was also in which might be an important factor idk  and the director announced that we had a playing test  It made me nervous just like anyone but it wasn t a difficult or long piece of music so I wasn t to worried and put it off  Now we come to the day of the test I m familiar with it but still don t want to do it  So one by one alphabetical order each persons plays  My hands are beyond sweaty as we approach the letter before mine  And we finally reach me I go to play and I just can t  it s like I forgot everything I knew and just froze still trying to keep it together I laugh it off little did I know how much that moment has affected me now       I m in my sophomore year now and moments like this still haunt me  I can barely talk to new people I have no social skills  Every time I have to do something solo I breakdown and can barely function  I hate it  I fear every social interaction now  It s halted my life I can t find anyone new or get a girlfriend  Every night it s the same question plaguing my mind  why choose me when you can have someone normal       It s hard to see any light when your at war with your head  I can t imagine living my whole life like this
